In a nutshell ...¶

make business recommendations

based on an analysis of transaction, web traffic and internet data

to a fast growing startup

Use exhaustive transaction data to get a detailed understanding of the business

Make recommendations on

  • clients targets
  • focused offering
  • further data collection

All in "lean startup" spirit...

Kombo¶

In [3]:
IFrame('https://www.kombo.co/en/app/outward/1/89m8s-auucv/83bw6-b4iyk/2020-03-06/Paris/Chamonix/results', width=800, height=700)
Out[3]:

a booking platform - not comparison site multimodal

business model¶

take advantage of transport liberalisation in Europe

  • bus
  • trains
  • planes coming soon

genuinely multimodal / multi-carrier

i.e recommend starting with a bus/train company and finishing with another

  • changing carrier can dramaticaly reduce price
  • 60% of bus tickets involve 2 carriers

differentiation¶

genuine European multimodal booking is unique¶

excellent technology¶

proof of concept¶

  • already largest reseller of Flixbus tickets in France
  • contract signed with railway companies in Spain, Italy, Germany
  • already high conversion rate
  • good capacity to raise funds at high valuation

Data¶

quality data¶

exhaustive :

  • bookings (checkout basket), including those not completed
  • tickets and
  • user data
  • for the past 3 years : approx 200-250k records

clean

  • acessible (SQL)
  • well formatted (limited preprocessing)
  • hardly any missing data

confidential - but no GDPR issues (emails anonymised)

t_df = pd.read_csv('tickets_booked_data.csv')
t_df.rename(columns={'ìdx`' : 'booking_id',
                    '`booking_id`' : 'company_id',
                     ' `company_id`' : 'departure_id',
                     ' `departure_id`' : 'arrival_id',
                     ' `arrival_id`' : 'departure_time', 
                      ' `departure_time`' : 'arrival_time',
                     ' `arrival_time`' : 'total_price',
                     ' `total_price`' : 'drop_me'
                     
                    }, 
            inplace=True)
t_df = t_df[~t_df.booking_id.str.startswith('INS')]
t_df.drop('drop_me', axis=1, inplace=True)
t_df['booking_id'] = t_df['booking_id'].str.replace('(','').astype(int)
t_df['company_id'] = t_df['company_id'].astype(int)
t_df['departure_id'] = t_df['departure_id'].astype(int)
t_df['arrival_id'] = t_df['arrival_id'].astype(int)
t_df['departure_time'] = t_df['departure_time'].str.replace('T',' ')
t_df['departure_time'] = pd.to_datetime(t_df['departure_time'], format=" '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'")
t_df['arrival_time'] = t_df['arrival_time'].str.replace('T',' ')
t_df['arrival_time'] = pd.to_datetime(t_df['arrival_time'], format=" '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'")
t_df['total_price'] = t_df['total_price'].str.replace(';','')
t_df['total_price'] = t_df['total_price'].str.replace(')','')
t_df['total_price'] = t_df['total_price'].astype(int)
